cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.DC 

This paper is about training convolutional neural networks with low bitwidth weights and activations using low bitwidth parameter gradients. This topic is closely related to computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG), as well as neural networks (cs.NE) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the implementation of bit convolutions on various hardware, which could fall under the category of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
